===============================================================================

  Be sure to have a copy of the Bootstrap stylesheet available on your app,
  you can get in on http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap.

  Inside your views, you can use the 'simple_form_for' with Bootstrap form
  classes, such as '.form-stacked', as the following:

    = simple_form_for(@user, :html => {:class => 'form-stacked' }) do |form|

===============================================================================